The paper deals with coded caching, which is a technique used in wireless networks to reduce network congestion during peak traffic times. This topic falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also presents several infinite classes of PDAs, which involve combinatorial designs and optimization, making it relevant to the sub-categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses lower bounds, which is a common theme in the statistical theory (cs.ST) sub-category.
